our writing workshops are one-hour group seminars that focus on specific writing topics . once you have registered for a workshop, you will receive an automated confirmation with the zoom link to join on the given date and time. you can also add the workshop to your calendar from the zoom link. we strongly recommend you add the workshop to your ical/calendar to receive reminder notifications ahead of time. click on the title of the workshop to register for the zoom session. trimming the fat: writing concisely and avoiding wordiness thursday, april 13, 2023 6:00 pm to 7:00 pm basic apa style monday, april 17, 2023 10:30 am to 11:30 am un-blurring plagiarism and paraphrasing wednesday, april 19, 2023 3:00 pm to 4:00 pm deconstructing the prompt tuesday, april 25, 2023 3:00 pm to 4:00 pm common grammar and punctuation errors wednesday, april 26, 2023 6:00 pm to 7:00 pm  provided you attended the full duration of the workshop (and did not leave early), any attendee who requires proof of attendance should complete the form link here http://bit.ly/wcworkshopconfirm . the request will be actioned within 1-3 working days. please arrive on time since workshops will begin promptly at the scheduled start time. we have a ; if you arrive after that initial grace period, you will not be able to attend the workshop. you can cancel your workshop registration at any time by clicking on the link in your registration confirmation email. so our facilitators know who will be attending each workshop session, we ask you to cancel your registration if you are unable to attend. if you do so far enough in advance, this will also allow another student to take your seat. the writing center reserves the right to cancel any workshop that does not have a minimum of five people enrolled 24 hours before the presentation start time. when you sign up for the workshop, you agree to our policies. please read our writing center policies and procedures . for other questions relating to the workshops, email writingcenter@sjsu.edu. phone: 408-924-2308 email: writingcenter@sjsu.edu for the fastest response, contact us via email . in your message, please include your sjsu id. dr. martin luther king, jr. library, 2nd floor one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0172 